## Evolution

This document evolves through the project lifecycle:
- **Created by:** `/pbr:begin` during project initialization
- **Updated by:** `/pbr:discuss` when requirements change or are reprioritized
- **Updated by:** `/pbr:build` when implementations complete (status column updates)
- **Referenced by:** `/pbr:verify` for completion checking

## Quality Criteria

A good REQUIREMENTS.md satisfies:
- [ ] Every requirement has a unique ID following the naming convention (REQ-F-NNN or REQ-NF-NNN)
- [ ] Every requirement is testable -- can write a pass/fail check for it
- [ ] Every In Scope item in PROJECT.md maps to at least one requirement here
- [ ] Traceability table is populated with phase assignments for all Must-priority requirements
- [ ] No orphan requirements (every REQ-ID appears in at least one plan's `implements:[]`)
- [ ] Status column is current (no stale "Open" for completed work)
